<html>
<body>
<p>Reports incorrect elements in Bean Validation <code>&lt;constraint-mappings&gt;</code> files:</p>

<ul>
  <li>References to non-instantiable classes</li>
  <li>References to classes that do not extend required class</li>
  <li>References to classes with inappropriate scope</li>
  <li>Empty tag and attribute values</li>
  <li>Tag and attribute values that do not match the required pattern (for example, Java Identifiers)</li>
  <li>Tags that do not include required children tags or attributes</li>
  <li>Tags that define objects with duplicate names</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
<pre><code>
&lt;constraint-mappings version="1.1"&gt;
    &lt;bean class="my.UserClass" ignore-annotations="false"&gt;
        &lt;field name="name"&gt;
            &lt;constraint annotation="<strong>java.lang.String</strong>"/&gt;  &lt;!--'java.lang.String' is not a Java Annotation --&gt;
        &lt;/field&gt;

        &lt;field name="name"&gt;
            &lt;constraint annotation="javax.validation.constraints.Size"&gt;
                &lt;element name="min"&gt;<strong>non-number</strong>&lt;/element&gt;    &lt;!--Should be a number from '-2,147,483,648' to '2,147,483,647' --&gt;
            &lt;/constraint&gt;
        &lt;/field&gt;

        &lt;getter name="<strong>zzz</strong>"&gt; Cannot resolve symbol 'zzz'
            &lt;valid/&gt;
        &lt;/getter&gt;

    &lt;/bean&gt;
&lt;/constraint-mappings&gt;
</code></pre>
</body>
</html>